# Walkthrough - Fixed Minecraft 1.19+ Launch Issue

The launch failure for Minecraft 1.19.1+ was caused by the launcher not handling the `logging` configuration required by newer versions.

## Changes

### 1. Model Updates in [GameInstance.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Models/GameInstance.cs)
Added [LogConfig](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Models/GameInstance.cs#54-60), [LogFile](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Models/GameInstance.cs#61-68), and `LogType` classes to represent the logging configuration structure found in `version.json`.

### 2. Service Updates in [GameService.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/GameService.cs)
Updated parser to read the `logging` section from the version JSON file and populate the [LogConfig](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Models/GameInstance.cs#54-60) property.

### 3. Launch Logic Updates in [LaunchService.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/LaunchService.cs)
- Added logic to verify and download the logging configuration file (XML) to `.minecraft/assets/log_configs/`.
- Added the `-Dlog4j.configurationFile` JVM argument to the launch command.

## Verification

### Manual Test
1.  **Launch 1.19.1**:
    - Select Minecraft 1.19.1.
    - Click "Start".
    - The launcher should now download the missing log config file (e.g., `client-1.12.xml`).
    - The game should launch successfully.
2.  **Verify Logs**:
    - Check `debug_launch_cmd.txt` in the game directory.
    - It should contain `-Dlog4j.configurationFile=...`.
